    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-09T10:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-09T10:41:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/460: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-09T17:00:00+01:19"
                            >July 9, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 9—11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Italo-Abyssinian Commission of Arbitration adjourned noon today. Abyssinian
                    agent insisted that jurisdiction of Commission permitted discussion of the
                    question of Abyssinian-Somaliland frontier line in connection with Walwal
                    incident, Italian Arbitrators insisted that procedure was incorrect and question
                    beyond jurisdiction of Commission. In this connection the Italian delegates
                    refused to agree to the appointment of a fifth arbitrator. The point has been
                    referred to the two Governments and the Secretary General of the League of
                    Nations has been informed. Professor Potter hopes that another meeting may be
                    held either here or in Italy on July 20th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Emmet</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
